                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-214-victim1896 t18270913-214-viclabel1213"></join>. On the 1st of September an officer produced two pairs of new shoes to me, which were mine, and have my initials on them; they were in the interior of my shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-214-person1897">
                  THOMAS 
                  PETO
               <interp inst="t18270913-214-person1897" type="surname" value="PETO"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-214-person1897" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-214-person1897" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker, and live at Hoxton. On the 30th of August, about one o'clock, Endersby brought this pair of shoes to me - Church was with him. I asked who they belonged to, he said to his father - I asked him for a better account; he said he would fetch his sister, who could tell me more about them - they then both ran away, leaving them with me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-214-person1898">
