                     <interp inst="t18270913-214-person1899" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I apprehended the prisoners in consequence of information. I had seen them together - I asked where they got the shoes; Endersby said they were his father's.</p>
               <p>ENDERSBY's Defence. I met Church in William-street; he asked me to pawn a pair of shoes for his aunt, and said he would give me half the money; he told me to say they were his father's, and that he lived in Willow-walk.</p>
